  "body": "In order for new Besu users to have a smooth experience, we should add a launcher script that allows them to set the most common options via the command line. \n\nOptions should include:\n* Network (incl. \"experimental networks\", such as YOLO, 1559 testnets, etc.) \n* Sync mode (maybe with a suggestion based on the network? e.g. fast sync for non-experimental networks, full sync for YOLO/1559/etc.)\n* Pruning on/off\n* JSON RPC on/off\n* GraphQL on/off\n* Websocket on/off\n* EthStats on/off \n* NAT on/off\n* Mining on/off \n\nWe should use errorprone to validate that the options are actually valid. \nThe launcher should create a config file and save it so users don't have to go through the launcher process again on 2nd launch. ",
